<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title><%= pageTitle %></title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/styles/main.css" />
  </head>
  <body data-page="<%= pageName %>">
    <%- include("partials/site-header", { pageName }) %>

    <main class="section-band">
      <article class="container policy-layout" aria-labelledby="policy-title">
        <p class="eyebrow" data-i18n="privacy.eyebrow">Privacy policy</p>
        <h1 id="policy-title" data-i18n="privacy.title">How Taskify handles local data.</h1>
        <p class="lede" data-i18n="privacy.subtitle">
          This coursework deployment keeps planning data on the current device and uses a small consent cookie to
          remember your banner choice.
        </p>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2 data-i18n="privacy.collectTitle">1. What we collect</h2>
          <p data-i18n="privacy.collectBody">
            Task titles, optional task details, priority, due date, language preference, and consent choice are stored
            in your browser. No analytics or third-party advertising scripts are enabled in this coursework build.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2 data-i18n="privacy.useTitle">2. How we use it</h2>
          <p data-i18n="privacy.useBody">
            Data is used to restore your board after refresh, keep the interface language consistent, and avoid showing
            the cookie banner on every visit once you choose an option.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2 data-i18n="privacy.cookieTitle">3. Cookie choices</h2>
          <p data-i18n="privacy.cookieBody">
            You can choose necessary only, reject optional cookies, or accept all. Because no optional tracking is
            bundled here, the difference is mainly whether we remember consent through the cookie banner.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="policy-section">
          <h2 data-i18n="privacy.contactTitle">4. Contact</h2>
          <p data-i18n="privacy.contactBody">
            For coursework review, contact the student team through the repository and include screenshots of the issue
            you observed.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </main>

    <%- include("partials/site-footer") %>
    <%- include("partials/cookie-banner") %>
    <script type="module" src="/static/js/site.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
